RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ON VACATION allowed to settle, saved ground along the first turn, advanced on the backstretch run, came within aim while two wide nearing the quarter marker, battled for the lead in mid-stretch, assumed command inside of the furlong pole and kept to task in the late stages to prevail. BEA MISCHIEF unhurried in the early stages, saved ground to the quarter marker, angled out in upper stretch, loomed nearing the furlong marker, could not keep pace with the winner in deep stretch and held for place. PEACEHAVEN rated off of the early pace, raced three wide along the first turn, stayed outside of rivals along the backstretch run, steered four wide on the second turn, closed well in the drive and just missed for place, while clear of the rest for show. KINDOFBLUEKITTEN saved ground in the early gong while on a snug early hold, was well positioned through the backstretch run, advanced two wide nearing the quarter marker, vied for the lead in the drive but could not sustain that run and weakened in the late stages. BOSSY PEGASUS showed early speed and cleared the field into the first turn, set moderate fractions to the quarter marker, was confronted by ON VACATION approaching the furlong grounds and gave way in the late stages. ACHROMATIC forwardly placed in the early going, stalked the moderate pace to the half-mile marker, raced three wide on the far turn, dropped back nearing the furlong pole and tired late. NATALIA shuffled at the start and was off slowly, allowed to settle, maintained a two wide path to the quarter marker and lacked a response in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Kindofbluekitten
ENTRY.COMMENT: snug hold early,stalked inside,2wide bid 1/4,vied,weakened late

ENTRY.NAME: Natalia
ENTRY.OWNER: Hammer Timothy J and Hammer Betty W
ENTRY.COMMENT: shuffled start,allowed to settle,2wide trip,no late rally

ENTRY.NAME: Peacehaven
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated off pace,3wide 1st turn,4wide 2nd turn,closed well,mssd 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 1M All Weather Track CR: 93. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500 OR LESS IN 2021 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races At A Mile Or Over Since November 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Such A Race S ince Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TROJAN CLUBHOUSE prominent in the early stages then assumed command along the first turn, carved out solid fractions while pressured through the backstretch run, held ALOHA KITTEN at bay to the furlong grounds and drew away in the late stages. ALOHA KITTEN forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked TROJAN CLUBHOUSE into the backstretch run then pressed that rival to the far turn, was held at bay to mid-stretch and could not match strides with the winner in the late going, while holding for place. ZABAVA rated off of the decent early fractions, maintained position through the backstretch run while well positioned, lost ground on the far turn, closed into the margin of the top two in the drive but lacked the needed late response. STOIC LUNA unhurried in the early stages, roused two then three wide on the far turn, Chavez lost his crop in upper stretch and lacked a rally in the final furlong. PREMIUMONSATURDAY allowed to settle, raced three wide into the far turn, swung widest for the drive and was not a factor. SHERILINDA stalked the decent early fractions while closest to the top pair, lost position into the far turn and tired in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Zabava
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated off pace,well placed,closed late,needed more

ENTRY.NAME: Premiumonsaturday
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle,3wide 2nd turn,swung widest,no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Aloha Kitten
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up,pressed pace,held at bay,turned away,held 2nd

ENTRY.NAME: Trojan Clubhouse
ENTRY.OWNER: Goat Racing Stables LLC and France Reid
ENTRY.COMMENT: showed speed,set pressured pace,repelled foe,drew away late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M All Weather Track CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOSHEWONT encountered traffic into the first turn and was shuffled to the rear in the early going, improved position along the backstretch run, continued that steady gain on the far turn, rallied five wide into the stretch run, came within aim of SMART KITTEN nearing the furlong pole, overtook the runner-up inside of the furlong marker and kicked clear in the late stages. SMART KITTEN showed early speed and assumed command into the first turn, set modest fractions while pressured through the backstretch run, shook free nearing the quarter marker, felt pressure from NOSHEWONT in mid-stretch, could not match strides with the winner inside of the furlong grounds but stayed on well in the end to be second best. MISS ACCELERATE prominent in the early stages, kept close attendance to SMART KITTEN through modest fractions to the half-mile marker, lost ground nearing the quarter pole, weakened in the drive and held well in the end to secure the show. LEXCELLENT allowed to settle in the early stages, raced three wide along the backstretch run, gained ground nearing the quarter marker, angled two wide for the drive and could not keep pace in the final furlong. A LITTLE GRACE stalked the early pace, advanced position along the backstretch run, well placed into the far turn, mounted a three wide bid to come within aim nearing the quarter marker and did not offer a rally in the stretch run. SUE GENEROUS forwardly placed into the first turn, was a bit keen while close up into the backstretch run, lost position nearing the half-mile marker, dropped back on the far turn and lacked a late response. HALLELUJAH BABY bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, was a bit keen while in traffic on the first turn, settled into the backstretch run, was outrun to the far turn and did not threaten in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Sue Generous
ENTRY.COMMENT: keen early,lost position 1/2,dropped back 2nd turn,no response

ENTRY.COMMENT: showed speed,set modest pace,caught 1/8,stayed on,2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Hallelujah Baby
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled start,keen early,no early speed,no threat

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 82. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EMILY SMILES forwardly placed in the early going, tracked the fast pace to the turn, advanced two wide nearing the quarter marker, confronted SPUN BEAUTIFUL leaving the turn, battled with that rival to the furlong grounds, shook free and drew away under hand urging in the final sixteenth. SPUN BEAUTIFUL broke alertly and showed early speed to assume command, set solid fractions to the quarter marker, was confronted by EMILY SMILES leaving the turn, battled with that rival to mid-stretch, could not keep pace in the late stages and just held for second. MAGICAL LADY crowded at the start by BOLD DAUGHTER and was off a step slowly, recovered and chased the leaders to the turn, raced two wide to the quarter marker, swung four wide for the drive, rallied in the late stages and just missed for place, while clear in the end for show. LION'S LAIR stalked the early pace, advanced while saving ground nearing the quarter marker, continued that bid to mid-stretch and gave way in the final furlong. HEAT SEEKING LETA lacked early speed, raced three wide into the drive and was not a late factor. BOLD DAUGHTER broke in at the start, crowded MAGICAL LADY and was off a step slowly, lacked early speed, dropped back on the turn and did not threaten in the drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Bold Daughter
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in start,no early speed,no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Spun Beautiful
ENTRY.OWNER: Hall Racing LLC Pearl Racing Titletown Racing Stables and West Point Thoroughbre

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace,gain 2wide turn,bid,shook free,drew away late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR. FIGHTER asked for early speed and was forwardly placed in the early stages, dueled outside of LOOKSGOODONYOUTHO to the turn, assumed command and extended the lead nearing the quarter pole, drew clear in upper stretch, had the margin cut into in the final sixteenth but kept to task to stay clear to the wire. PRACTICAL BID bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, recovered to chase the pace to the turn, lost ground nearing the quarter marker, swung four wide for the stretch run, closed with good interest in the drive, was not able to impact the winner in deep stretch but finished well to earn the place. PERFORMATIVE chased the solid early pace, was green and climbed in the running into the turn, was floated out a bit by LOOKSGOODONYOUTHO in upper stretch, closed in the final furlong but was outkicked in deep stretch and held for show in the late stages. LOOKSGOODONYOUTHO broke alertly, dueled for early pace duties with MR. FIGHTER, lost ground to that foe on the turn, floated PERFORMATIVE out a bit at the top of the lane, weakened in the stretch drive and was outfinished for third. MR BIG DEAL lacked early speed, raced four wide into the drive and did not factor. TIGER HEAT unprepared at the start and spotted the field leaving the break, trailed to the turn, improved position nearing the quarter marker, ran evenly to mid-stretch and did not threaten in the late stages. LIL KOWBOY showed brief foot in the early stages, could not keep pace to the turn and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 74. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $2,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GARDEES WORLD engaged with WICKED SUNSET for the early lead then took command approaching the turn, sped to a clear lead nearing the quarter marker, widened the margin nearing the furlong pole and kept to task in the late stages to be much the best. SILK ROAD SALLY allowed to settle in the early stages, raced two wide to the quarter marker, ran evenly to mid-stretch, closed well in the late stages while on the left lead, was no match for the winner in deep stretch but stayed on to hold safely for second. BOUNDFORJAMAICA chased the fast early pace, was outrun on the turn while three wide, swung four wide into the lane, finished evenly in the drive and kept on to secure third. WICKED SUNSET broke alertly, engaged with GARDEES WORLD to contest the early pace, ceded the lead to that rival heading to the turn, chased to the quarter marker, was outrun in upper stretch, weakened in the drive and was outfinished for third. CLOCHARD STREET bobbled at the start, hit the gate and was off awkwardly, recovered to chase the fast early pace, lost ground while four wide on the turn, gave way in upper stretch and lacked a late response. HALF HOPING allowed to settle in the early stages, came five wide to the quarter marker and did not offer a late response. KISS RIDE GOODBYE lacked early speed and was not a factor. DANGEROUS ILLUSION chased the fast early pace, lost ground while chasing from the rail on the turn, could not keep pace in the drive and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Boundforjamaica
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace,2wide turn,evenly,kept on for show

ENTRY.NAME: Clochard Street
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled start,hit gate,chased,lost ground 4wide turn,gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Silk Road Sally
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle,2wide turn,evenly to 1/8,no match,closed 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 6F All Weather Track CR: 105. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 32000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $62,500. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since November 1 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR RACER settled off of the decent early fractions, saved ground along the turn, tipped out two wide at the top of the stretch, chased WAR GAMES to the furlong pole, collared that rival nearing the sixteenth-marker and drove clear under firm hand urging in deep stretch. RAGER unhurried in the early stages, raced two wide to the quarter marker while not far back, slipped to the rail in upper stretch, gained ground nearing the furlong pole, shifted out inside of the furlong marker, was outkicked in deep stretch by STAR RACER but closed in the late stages to secure second. IRREFUTABLE broke alertly, took back and stalked the decent early pace, raced two wide to the quarter pole, lost ground nearing mid-stretch, was outfinished in the late stages and held for third. WAR GAMES sent to establish the early lead, set decent fractions while rating on the front end, drew to a clear advantage nearing the quarter marker, was set down for the drive and maintained a clear lead to mid-stretch but could not hold off STAR RACER inside of the furlong pole and weakened. MY SUMMER DREAM tracked the decent early pace, raced three wide to the quarter marker, could not keep pace in the drive and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Star Racer
ENTRY.OWNER: Blue Moon Racing Ltd and Dietrich Steven

ENTRY.NAME: Rager
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried,not far back,inside bid,shift out 1/8,closed for 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 6F All Weather Track CR: 73. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARY WALKER broke outward at the start, was content to track the pace down the backstretch and through the turn, quickened approaching the quarter pole, battled with OTTER POP the length of the stretch run and managed to out-finish that one despite drifting out to the middle of the track under left-handed encouragement. OTTER POP broke alertly and went for the lead while angling towards the rail, held a clear advantage to the head of the stretch, was challenged on the outside by MARY WALKER, dueled that one to deep stretch and was outfinished. SASSY TINKERBELL broke a bit slow and was fighting the rider and hard to place in the run down the backstretch, settled down on the turn but had only one horse beat to the quarter pole, waited for racing room at the top of the stretch and kept to task when clear finishing well enough to gain third. CUTE RENEGADE broke in a bit and brushed with LUCKY LOCKETT at the break, then was bumped hard by that one and forced towards the gap, losing momentum and a few lengths to the rest of the field, chased the field to the turn, began to improve position passing the three-eighths pole despite a wide trip then made a good run down the stretch to just miss out on a minor award. SHE'S FANCY LIKE broke with the pack but pushed to keep up through the first quarter mile, came under heavy pressure from the half-mile pole, was four-wide into the stretch and finished one-paced. AWESOME MAUI GIRL raced in mid-pack through the early going, was still with a chance at the quarter pole but was unable to find another gear when needed in the stretch. LUCKY LOCKETT broke in at the break brushing with CUTE RENEGATE, those two came together again a few strides later with the latter getting bumped towads the gap, rushed up along the rail to contest the early pace, settled for a stalking position on the turn tipped out a path for the stretch run but had nothing left.

ENTRY.NAME: Cute Renegade
ENTRY.OWNER: Conner Dennis Jacobsen Wade and McKeen Michael
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped hard into gap, chased, sustained rally from 3/8

ENTRY.NAME: Lucky Lockett
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed, bumped rival start, forward early, faltered stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Awesome Maui Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid-pack early, saved ground, no response when last 1/4

ENTRY.NAME: Sassy Tinkerbell
ENTRY.COMMENT: hard to place backstretch run, waited, kept on through stretch

ENTRY.NAME: She's Fancy Like
ENTRY.COMMENT: under pressure early, mild mid-race move, one-paced late

ENTRY.NAME: Otter Pop
ENTRY.OWNER: Thomas A Farrell Bypass Trust and MJVET Stables
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace to 1/4, dueled rival to deep stretch, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Mary Walker
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out start, tracked, bid 1/4, stretch duel, drifted out late
